Australia captain Ricky Ponting won
the toss and elected to bat first against India in the series-
opening cricket Test in Mohali.  India, the No. 1-ranked Test team, holds the Border-
Gavaskar Trophy after a 2-0 win at home two years ago. Australia
is the only team to have won a Test series in India during the
past 10 years.  If Australia loses the two-match contest, it will fall one
place to fifth in the International Cricket Councilâ€™s rankings
and begin the Ashes series ranked lower than England.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
